13 Section 1. Section 20-5-420, MCA, is amended to read:
14 "20-5-420. Self-administration or possession of asthma, severe allergy, or anaphylaxis
15 medication -- definitions. (1) As used in 20-5-421, [section 2], and this section, the following definitions apply:
16 (a) "Anaphylaxis" means a systemic allergic reaction that can be fatal in a short time period and is
17 also known as anaphylactic shock.
18 (b) "Asthma" means a chronic disorder or condition of the lungs that requires lifetime, ongoing
19 medical intervention.
20 (c) "Authorized personnel" means an employee or agent identified by a school who is approved by
21 the school administrator to administer a stock medication in a school setting or at a related activity pursuant to
22 20-5-421, [section 2], or 20-5-426.
23 (c)(d) "Medication" means a medicine, including inhaled bronchodilators, inhaled corticosteroids, and
24 autoinjectable epinephrine, prescribed by a licensed physician as defined in 37-3-102, a physician assistant
25 who has been authorized to prescribe medications as provided in 37-20-404, or an advanced practice
26 registered nurse with prescriptive authority as provided in 37-8-202(1)(h).
27 (e) "Respiratory distress" means a person's inability to breathe adequately, including the perceived
28 or actual presence of associated symptoms such as coughing, wheezing, or shortness of breath.
