4 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Emergency use of stock albuterol in school setting -- limit on
5 liability -- reporting. A public or nonpublic school may maintain a supply of stock albuterol, including single-
6 use disposable holding chambers if necessary, to be administered by a school nurse or other authorized
7 personnel to a student or nonstudent as needed for respiratory distress. A school that intends to obtain an order
8 for emergency use of stock albuterol in a school setting or at related activities shall adhere to the following
9 requirements:
10 (1) A school that keeps stock albuterol on site shall develop a protocol related to the training of
11 school employees, the maintenance and location of the stock albuterol, and the immediate and long-term
12 followup to the administration of the medication, including determining when to make a 9-1-1 emergency call.
13 (2) The stock albuterol must be prescribed by a physician, advanced practice registered nurse, or
14 physician assistant. The school must be designated as the patient and each prescription for stock albuterol
15 must be filled by a licensed pharmacy.
16 (3) A licensed pharmacist may dispense stock albuterol medication and spacers to schools in
17 accordance with this section.
18 (4) A school may enter into an agreement with a manufacturer of bronchodilators or spacers, a
19 third-party supplier of bronchodilator or spacers, or a health care office to obtain bronchodilators or spacers at
20 no charge, at market price, or at a reduced price. A school district may accept gifts, grants, or donations to
21 purchase bronchodilators or spacers for emergency use.
22 (5) Authorized personnel shall complete an annual asthma education program approved by the
23 department of public health and human services. The training must include causes of respiratory distress,
24 recognition of signs and symptoms of respiratory distress, indications for the administration of albuterol,
25 administration techniques, and the need for immediate access to a certified emergency responder.
26 (6) The stock albuterol must be kept in a secure and easily accessible location.
27 (7) A school nurse or other authorized personnel may, in good faith, administer the stock albuterol
28 to any student or nonstudent who is experiencing respiratory distress based on the protocol developed by the
